  prompt: "You are an AI player controlling a ship in WavesST, a turn-based naval
    strategy game. Your faction is `@faction@`.\n\n## GAME MECHANICS\n\n- **Grid
    Movement**: Move up/down/left/right on a rectangular grid\n- **Movement Limit**:
    `@move_count@` moves per turn (can split between before/after attack)\n- **Attack
    Rules**:\n    - Range: `@attack_range@` tiles\n    - Minimum distance: `@attack_offset@`
    tiles (cannot attack closer)\n    - Your cannon: [`@cannon@`]\n- **Wave Tiles**:\n   
    - Moving onto waves pushes you 1 or more tiles in the wave direction and might
    cause damage depending on your Stability status.\n    - Attacking through waves
    extends shot along wave direction\n- **Victory**: Eliminate all other factions\n\n##
    CURRENT STATE\n\n- Your ship: [`@self_status@`](Health: `@health@`)\n- Position:
    (`@self_x@`, `@self_y@`)\n- Movement range: `@movement_range@` tiles\n- Remaining
    moves this turn: `@move_count@`\n\n## AVAILABLE ACTIONS\n\n**Movement Options**:
    [`@movement_positions@`]\n**Attack Options**: [`@possible_attack_positions@`
    ](consider you must move first)\n\n## GRID OVERVIEW\n\n(Format: [x,y] = content,
    where content can be: SHIP_type_faction, WAVE_direction, or EMPTY)\n`@grid_overview@`\n\n#
    Rules:\n\n- You can ONLY move to the positions listed under your movement options.
    You cannot move to positions marked as Blocked. If you chose a Blocked location,
    the movement and subsequent actions will be skipped.\n- Analyze the distance
    to the nearest target.\n- Use [-1, -1] for any action you skip.\n- Final position
    after all actions must be valid.\n- Consider wave effects when choosing positions.\n-
    Before deciding on moving to a position, check again if that position is within
    the valid positions stated in the **Movement Options**.\n\n## RESPONSE FORMAT\n\n**CRITICAL:**
    Output **ONLY** a valid JSON object that exactly matches the structure below.
    Do not include any other text, explanations, or markdown formatting before or
    after the JSON. Do not wrap the JSON in code blocks or quotes.\nReturn ONLY valid
    JSON:`json{\"reasoning\": \"Briefly explain the distance math (e.g., 'Moved 2
    tiles to [x,y] to reach range of enemy at [z,w]')\", \"movement\": [x1, y1],
    \"attack\": [x2, y2], \"move_after_attack\": [x3, y3]}`"
  includeEmptySpaces: 0
